"create","databaseId":{"__rl":true,"mode":"list","value":"","cachedResultName":"Asset Database"},"title":"={{ $json.price || $json.symbol }}","options":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.notion","typeVersion":2.2,"position":[10098,1420],"id":"6d7579ad-8556-41d0-b41c-97c2ccbd5e6b","name":"Park in Dead-Letter Queue","retryOnFail":true,"maxTries":3,"waitBetweenTries":2000},{"parameters":{"content":"### Every Few Minutes\n\nStarts the workflow on a timer — every 10 min. No input data; downstream nodes fetch what they need.\n\nNext: Fetch Current Metrics","width":280,"height":232,"color":5},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-330,520],"id":"3a6e46b7-52d0-1e26-71e4-ad27d07921d2","name":"Note: Every Few Minutes"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Fetch Current Metrics\n\nGET https://api.example.com/v1/assets — retries 3× with backoff on failure.\n\nPorts: ①→ Compute Severity Signals · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 API key / bearer for the target API","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-6,520],"id":"18d67e2b-6d2f-7f93-2d64-a96de106264a","name":"Note: Fetch Current Metrics"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Compute Severity Signals\n\nCustom JavaScript: Compute a simple moving average and momentum signal\n\nNext: Grade Severity Tier","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[318,520],"id":"ef39de30-3cbf-6777-41e5-a835c32a6da8","name":"Note: Compute Severity Signals"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Grade Severity Tier\n\nRoutes each item to one of 4 lanes: info, warning, critical + fallback.\n\nPorts: ①→ Just Record (Info) · ②→ Warn Channel (Slack) · ③→ Page Urgently (Telegram) · ④→ Archive Unscored","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[642,520],"id":"b4797082-3555-582d-7f70-50fb221b4ce2","name":"Note: Grade Severity Tier"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Just Record (Info)\n\nCreates a new page in the Notion database — the title is pulled straight from the item's key field.\n\nPorts: ①→ Merge Tier Outcomes · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Notion integration token","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[966,40],"id":"1e5aafdb-fff7-fcc3-d5e9-5b8398464e1d","name":"Note: Just Record (Info)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Warn Channel (Slack)\n\nPosts a message to Slack (`#trading`) — a low-latency way for the team to see automation activity without checking a dashboard.\n\nPorts: ①→ Merge Tier Outcomes · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1290,520],"id":"5ee826cb-0067-d86f-c168-e012c9d3d011","name":"Note: Warn Channel (Slack)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Page Urgently (Telegram)\n\nSends a Telegram message to the configured chat — the same bot can also receive replies, so this doubles as a two-way ops channel.\n\nPorts: ①→ Merge Tier Outcomes · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Telegram bot token","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1614,1000],"id":"e23ab3f0-9ea1-3b3e-0af5-e847fc34d15a","name":"Note: Page Urgently (Telegram)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Archive Unscored\n\nCreates a new page in the Notion database — the title is pulled straight from the item's key field.\n\nPorts: ①→ Merge Tier Outcomes · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Notion integration token","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1938,1480],"id":"ee2e9002-3f3e-79a9-5fc5-91b771d60e45","name":"Note: Archive Unscored"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Merge Tier Outcomes\n\nRejoins 4 branches into one stream (mode: append) so downstream logic runs once.\n\nNext: Stamp Completion Time","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[2586,520],"id":"2162290e-b61e-8606-57e7-e2aa996cfcf3","name":"Note: Merge Tier Outcomes"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Stamp Completion Time\n\nStamps `completedAt` with the current time for auditing.\n\nNext: Persist Run Metadata","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[3558,520],"id":"0a570049-4be9-80b1-e705-a737666dd05f","name":"Note: Stamp Completion Time"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Persist Run Metadata\n\nSaves key fields onto the execution record — searchable later in n8n's execution list.\n\nNext: Load Previous Snapshot","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[3882,520],"id":"3e86d689-106d-12fd-7fb2-a8ab0cdd8617","name":"Note: Persist Run Metadata"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Load Previous Snapshot\n\nPulls every page from the Notion database — fine for small datasets; add a filter if the database grows large.\n\nPorts: ①→ Compute Drift vs Snapshot · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Notion integration token","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4206,520],"id":"bb87f973-9f84-d806-81be-a2b906d380db","name":"Note: Load Previous Snapshot"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Compute Drift vs Snapshot\n\nCustom JavaScript: Compare current metrics with the previous snapshot\n\nNext: Fingerprint for Idempotency","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4530,520],"id":"eb732e21-a734-4101-39ec-2a2652028257","name":"Note: Compute Drift vs Snapshot"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Fingerprint for Idempotency\n\nCustom JavaScript: Build a stable idempotency key per asset (djb2 hash, no deps)\n\nNext: Drop Already-Processed Items","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4854,520],"id":"6b243f75-ba90-0af8-8750-9a81fce6e8de","name":"Note: Fingerprint for Idempotency"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Drop Already-Processed Items\n\nCross-execution dedupe: remembers keys it has processed before and drops repeats — the idempotency guard.\n\nNext: Offload to Post-Process Sub-workflow","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5178,520],"id":"8a131218-8cc4-a37f-4447-1a818127fc1b","name":"Note: Drop Already-Processed Items"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Offload to Post-Process Sub-workflow\n\nDelegates to a reusable sub-workflow (single-responsibility building block) and waits for its result.\n\nPorts: ①→ Record Sub-workflow Result · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5502,520],"id":"8fa8f6ad-5d1f-5390-3805-912288a99e89","name":"Note: Offload to Post-Process Sub-workflow"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Record Sub-workflow Result\n\nSaves key fields onto the execution record — searchable later in n8n's execution list.\n\nNext: Enrich with Reference Data","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5826,520],"id":"14194a9c-81b2-0deb-e15a-972ebe67ade1","name":"Note: Record Sub-workflow Result"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Enrich with Reference Data\n\nGET https://enrichment.example.com/v2/lookup — retries 3× with backoff on failure.\n\nPorts: ①→ Fold In Enrichment Fields · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 API key / bearer for the target API","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[6150,520],"id":"bd47d36c-cc56-b7f6-d3c7-c034dc03d079","name":"Note: Enrich with Reference Data"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Fold In Enrichment Fields\n\nShapes the item: writes `enrichedAt`, `enrichmentSource`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Serialize Run Output (CSV)","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[6474,520],"id":"4836a2f5-8be6-0af2-ff78-548876b9d4bd","name":"Note: Fold In Enrichment Fields"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Serialize Run Output (CSV)\n\nSerializes items to a CSV binary file.\n\nNext: Archive Row Snapshot","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[6798,520],"id":"2567662a-d6b6-f30a-3b6d-e80f545212a3","name":"Note: Serialize Run Output (CSV)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Archive Row Snapshot\n\nAppends a new row to 'Asset Tracker' — a human-readable audit trail that doesn't require opening n8n to inspect.\n\nPorts: ①→ Align Field Names · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[7122,520],"id":"43c3bb8f-0745-5431-44bb-0eab13ea03e7","name":"Note: Archive Row Snapshot"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Align Field Names\n\nNormalizes field names so every source feeds the same downstream schema.\n\nNext: Tag Pipeline Metadata","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[7446,520],"id":"c4fcfaf4-8c94-13c3-c98a-08de2d1f994c","name":"Note: Align Field Names"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Tag Pipeline Metadata\n\nShapes the item: writes `pipeline`, `version`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Guard Non-Empty price","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[7770,520],"id":"2df29d66-30ed-c7be-cabc-33b48bc06fc6","name":"Note: Tag Pipeline Metadata"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Guard Non-Empty price\n\nDrops items that fail the condition; only qualifying items continue (no false branch).\n\nNext: Cap Batch Volume","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[8094,520],"id":"7652c8f2-3908-dc63-c6e8-9051f20e2dd5","name":"Note: Guard Non-Empty price"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Cap Batch Volume\n\nCaps the stream at 25 items to protect downstream quotas.\n\nNext: Stamp Processing Time","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[8418,520],"id":"b8c45a50-344c-ba88-19a2-9bb9b1db35e4","name":"Note: Cap Batch Volume"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Stamp Processing Time\n\nStamps `processedAt` with the current time for auditing.\n\nNext: Sort Assets Newest First","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[8742,520],"id":"5601298e-9b6a-72af-caa3-2c65fcf23503","name":"Note: Stamp Processing Time"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Sort Assets Newest First\n\nOrders items (newest first) so limits and digests pick the most relevant records.\n\nNext: Summarize Run Stats","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[9066,520],"id":"804e0bf6-5084-4703-d5c1-5f656547d510","name":"Note: Sort Assets Newest First"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Summarize Run Stats\n\nShapes the item: writes `runAt`, `itemCount`, `status`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[9390,520],"id":"9f5ca7e8-4851-6a88-0c2f-1b9903f560c3","name":"Note: Summarize Run Stats"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)\n\nAppends a new row to 'Asset Tracker' — a human-readable audit trail that doesn't require opening n8n to inspect.\n\nPorts: ①→ Send Summary to Telegram · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[9714,520],"id":"cb9af45c-ee43-1791-ea12-63dfc6058f49","name":"Note: Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Send Summary to Telegram\n\nSends a Telegram message to the configured chat — the same bot can also receive replies, so this doubles as a two-way ops channel.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Telegram bot token","width":280,"height":232,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[10038,520],"id":"ed48cd4e-4257-5a79-8220-2f28161fcf52","name":"Note: Send Summary to Telegram"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Capture Failure Context\n\nShapes the item: writes `failedNode`, `errorMessage`, `workflow`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Escalate Failure to Telegram","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[9390,1540],"id":"9e442378-425a-92e4-55a9-e8e02fdd4730","name":"Note: Capture Failure Context"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Escalate Failure to Telegram\n\nSends a Telegram message to the configured chat — the same bot can also receive replies, so this doubles as a two-way ops channel.\n\nNext: Park in Dead-Letter Queue\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 Telegram bot token","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[9714,1540],"id":"38045601-0a8d-73a8-978a-46afa30f61fc","name":"Note: Escalate Failure to Telegram"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Park in Dead-Letter Queue\n\nCreates a new page in the Notion database — the title is pulled straight from the item's key field.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 Notion integration token","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[10038,1540],"id":"97419ece-e6be-cf0c-6481-80f45805df9a","name":"Note: Park in Dead-Letter Queue"},{"parameters":{"content":"# Watch stock levels with HTTP / REST API and Telegram\n\n**Pattern:** Threshold Monitoring · **Level:** Architect · **Trigger:** Scheduled\n\n## What it does\nWatch stock levels with HTTP / REST API and Telegram. It runs automatically on a schedule.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual risk monitoring is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nEvery Few Minutes → Fetch Current Metrics → Compute Severity Signals → Grade Severity Tier → Just Record (Info) → Merge Tier Outcomes → Stamp Completion Time → …\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to threshold monitoring without manual effort\n- Anyone automating risk monitoring in finance\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Keeps your systems in sync\n- Responds in seconds\n- Removes copy-paste errors\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: API key / bearer for the target API; Google OAuth2 / service account; Notion integration token; Slack OAuth2; Telegram bot token.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.\n\n## Try it now\nSample data is pinned on the trigger — hit **Execute Workflow** to watch it flow through every node before connecting any real credentials. Unpin the trigger (right-click → Unpin) when you're ready to go live.","width":480,"height":900},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-830,80],"id":"cf45b95e-a2fc-1718-6b40-eecaf178d392","name":"📘 Workflow Overview"},{"parameters":{"content":"## Design decisions\n\nThree response tiers, not a single yes/no alert, match the response to the severity — logging every metric quietly would bury the one critical spike, and paging on-call for every info-level blip trains them to ignore alerts entirely. Critical gets a distinct, louder channel from warning on purpose.","width":480,"height":300,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-830,1020],"id":"5a16bb07-ae28-d256-9d88-a2a672e024c1","name":"🎓 Design Decisions"},{"parameters":{"content":"## Practice exercises\n\nAbout as deep as this pattern goes — extend it:\n\n1. Adjust the tier thresholds and see how alert sensitivity changes.\n2. Trigger a critical-tier value and confirm it pages a different channel than warning does.\n3. Add a 4th tier between warning and critical.","width":480,"height":340,"color":6},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-830,1360],"id":"d01d87f9-985d-76bd-5717-ad0ceb3ae6f8","name":"🧪 Practice Exercises"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🛟 Error handling & retries\n\nExternal calls retry **3× with 2s backoff**. Anything still failing exits through its node's error output into the red error rail → context is captured and the on-call channel is alerted. Failures are also parked in a dead-letter queue for replay. Set an n8n **Error Workflow** in settings as the final safety net.","width":360,"height":260,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-230,-500],"id":"36fb5c21-07c8-34e4-27e5-fdde07bb85de","name":"🛟 Error handling & retries"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🧹 Data quality\n\nDedupe/diff steps make re-runs safe: the same input twice will not create duplicate records. If you change the key fields, clear n8n's dedupe memory (node → 'Clear stored keys') before the next run.","width":360,"height":260,"color":1},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[190,-500],"id":"925a51a9-b250-1490-4025-7970aa50c530","name":"🧹 Data quality"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🛠 Customize me\n\nQuick wins: point the data nodes at your own accounts (see 🔑 lines on each card), adjust the trigger cadence, and tune thresholds/labels to your risk monitoring process. Every node card explains its role — safe to extend at any marked branch.","width":360,"height":260,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[610,-500],"id":"0c58dd62-ba0b-23b5-1002-d7ff56895a31","name":"🛠 Customize me"}],"connections":{"Every Few Minutes":{"main":[[{"node":"Fetch Current Metrics","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Fetch Current Metrics":{"main":[[{"node":"Compute Severity Signals","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Compute Severity Signals":{"main":[[{"node":"Grade Severity Tier","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Grade Severity Tier":{"main":[[{"node":"Just Record (Info)","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Warn Channel (Slack)","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Page Urgently (Telegram)","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Archive Unscored","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Just Record (Info)":{"main":[[{"node":"Merge Tier Outcomes","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Warn Channel (Slack)":{"main":[[{"node":"Merge Tier Outcomes","type":"main","index":1}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Page Urgently (Telegram)":{"main":[[{"node":"Merge Tier Outcomes","type":"main","index":2}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Archive Unscored":{"main":[[{"node":"Merge Tier Outcomes","type":"main","index":3}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Merge Tier Outcomes":{"main":[[{"node":"Stamp Completion Time","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Stamp Completion Time":{"main":[[{"node":"Persist Run Metadata","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Persist Run Metadata":{"main":[[{"node":"Load Previous Snapshot","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Load Previous Snapshot":{"main":[[{"node":"Compute Drift vs Snapshot","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Compute Drift vs Snapshot":{"main":[[{"node":"Fingerprint for Idempotency","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Fingerprint for Idempotency":{"main":[[{"node":"Drop Already-Processed Items","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Drop Already-Processed Items":{"main":[[{"node":"Offload to Post-Process Sub-workflow","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Offload to Post-Process Sub-workflow":{"main":[[{"node":"Record Sub-workflow Result","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Record Sub-workflow Result":{"main":[[{"node":"Enrich with Reference Data","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Enrich with Reference Data":{"main":[[{"node":"Fold In Enrichment Fields","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Fold In Enrichment Fields":{"main":[[{"node":"Serialize Run Output (CSV)","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Serialize Run Output (CSV)":{"main":[[{"node":"Archive Row Snapshot","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Archive Row Snapshot":{"main":[[{"node":"Align Field Names","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Align Field Names":{"main":[[{"node":"Tag Pipeline Metadata","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Tag Pipeline Metadata":{"main":[[{"node":"Guard Non-Empty price","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Guard Non-Empty price":{"main":[[{"node":"Cap Batch Volume","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Cap Batch Volume":{"main":[[{"node":"Stamp Processing Time","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Stamp Processing Time":{"main":[[{"node":"Sort Assets Newest First","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Sort Assets Newest First":{"main":[[{"node":"Summarize Run Stats","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Summarize Run Stats":{"main":[[{"node":"Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)":{"main":[[{"node":"Send Summary to Telegram","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Capture Failure Context":{"main":[[{"node":"Escalate Failure to Telegram","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Escalate Failure to Telegram":{"main":[[{"node":"Park in Dead-Letter Queue","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Send Summary to Telegram":{"main":[[],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]}},"active":false,"settings":{"executionOrder":"v1","saveDataErrorExecution":"all","saveManualExecutions":true,"executionTimeout":3600},"meta":{"templateCredsSetupCompleted":false},"tags":[],"pinData":{"Every Few Minutes":[{"json":{"symbol":"BTC-USD","price":64250.1,"change24h":2.3,"volume":28450000000}},{"json":{"symbol":"ETH-USD","price":3180.55,"change24h":-1.1,"volume":12300000000}}]},"versionId":"a8a5375e-14a9-415d-aa43-c0f867a32f9a","id":"FDX08768"}